"Object Editor Help"
Message
"The green cube is the axis point of your object, draw around it.\nUse arrow keys or mouse to rotate the camera, [W] and [S] to zoom [T] and [G] to zoom slowly (Linear movement [R] Up [F] Down [D] Right [A] Left.)\n[ESC] to toggle between mouse moving mode and mouse pointer mode\n[SPACE] to place a cube and [E] to erase a cube [Q] to steal the properties of the cube infront of you.\n[Z] and [X] to do a barrel roll spin like an airplane, [N] to stablelize the camera(Use this when you are facing at an object at a weird angle).\n[M] to switch between static and  moving camera drawing modes.\nIn Static camera mode, arrows move up down left right [W] moves forward [S] moves back.\nAfter changin a property, click the center of the screen to continue placing cubes."

value
'This line is intentially long to test movement of gj and gk over wrapped lines. I will start on the end of this line, then make a step up and back to set the origin for j and k.\nThis line is supposed to be even longer than the previous. I will jump here and make another wiggle with gj and gk, before I jump back to the line above. Both wiggles should not change my cursor\'s target character but both j/k and gj/gk change each other\'s reference position.'

'2,3sort'

'2sort'

'b\nZ\na\na\nd\na\nc\na'
'ex_sort_decimal'
'sort d'
'd3\n s5\n6\n.9'
'6\nd3\n s5\n.9'
'ex_sort_decimal_negative'
'z-9\nd3\n s5\n6\n.9'
'6\nd3\n s5\n.9\nz-9'

'.9\n6\n s5\nd3'
'6\nd3\n s5\n.9'

' s5\n6\n.9\n&0xB\nd3'
'6\nd3\n s5\n&0xB\n.9'

'6\nd3\n s5\n.9\n.8'

'y\nz\nc1\nb2\na3'

'sort! d'
'a3\nb2\nc1\nz\ny'

"Serves files on the given hostname and port, defaulting to"
" localhost:3000."
"-c, --compile"
"Shortcut to run nodefront compile -w/--watch"
" simultaneously"
"Should be used with the -c/--compile"
" option. Put compiled files in the given directory, passing this to the"
" -o/--output option of the compile command. Defaults to the current"
" directory."
"-l, --live"
"Automatically refreshes the browser upon"
" modification of HTML/CSS/JS files."
".nf/serve"
"./commands/serve"
"fetch [library]"
"Fetches <library> for immediate use."
"-u, --url <url>"
"The URL to fetch the library from."
"-p, --path <pathRegex>"
"Provides the path to the library in the"
" zip archive specified by the -u/--url <url> parameter. Note"
" that <pathRegex> should be a regular expression."
"-v, --version <version>"
"Specify the version of the library to"
" fetch."
""
"If provided, the library will be"
" stored as a file in the given directory. Otherwise, it will be"
" added to the current directory."
""
"-t, --type <type>"
"The type of this library, which should also"
"be its extension. This defaults to js."
"js"
"-m, --minify"
"Minify the fetched file."
"-i, --interactive"
"Interactively add a new library and fetch it."
".nf/fetch"
"./commands/fetch"
"insert <library> <file>"
"Inserts <library> into <file>. <library> should be a path to"
"a CSS/JavaScript library and <file> should be a path to an"
"HTML/Jade document."
"-h, --head"
"Insert the given JS file into the head of the"
"document. By default, JS is inserted into the footer."
"-a, --absolute"
"Use an absolute path for the inserted"
"link/script tag instead of a relative one."
"-t, --tab-length <length>"
"The number of spaces that constitute"
" each tab in the document for insertion purposes. If hard tabs"
" are used, specify -1 for this option. Otherwise, if this is not"
" given, the tab length is assumed to be 4."
